eh","line":117},{"title":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","target":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","line":118},{"title":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","target":"Author/Ko-Chao Lee","line":119},{"title":"Author/Hsiang-Lan Kuo","target":"Author/Hsiang-Lan Kuo","line":120},{"title":"Author/Hsiang-Lan Kuo","target":"Author/Hsiang-Lan Kuo","line":121},{"title":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","target":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","line":122},{"title":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","target":"Author/Li-Ya Lee","line":123},{"title":"Author/Wanping Chen","target":"Author/Wanping Chen","line":124},{"title":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","line":125},{"title":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","line":126},{"title":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","target":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","line":127},{"title":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","target":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","line":128},{"title":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","target":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","line":129},{"title":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","target":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","line":130},{"title":"Author/Shui-Yi Tung","target":"Author/Shui-Yi Tung","line":131},{"title":"Author/Shui-Yi Tung","target":"Author/Shui-Yi Tung","line":132},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/kuo_comparative_2017/kuo_comparative_2017.pdf","line":134}],"metadata":{"id":"kuo_comparative_2017","type":"article-journal","title":"A Comparative Proteomic Analysis of Erinacine A's Inhibition of Gastric Cancer Cell Viability and Invasiveness.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2017]]},"DOI":"10.1159/000480338","container-title":"Cellular Physiology and Biochemistry","abstract":"Background / Aims: Erinacine A, isolated from the ethanol extract of the Hericium erinaceus mycelium, has been demonstrated as a new alternative anticancer medicine. Drawing upon current research, this study presents an investigation of the molecular mechanism of erinacine A inhibition associated with gastric cancer cell growth. Methods: Cell viability was determined by Annexin V–FITC/propidium iodide staining and migration using a Boyden chamber assay to determine the effects of erinacine A treatment on the proliferation capacity and invasiveness of gastric cancer cells. A proteomic assay provided information that was used to identify the differentially-expressed proteins following erinacine A treatment, as well as the mechanism of its targets in the apoptotic induction of erinacine A. Results: Our results demonstrate that erinacine A treatment of TSGH 9201 cells increased cytotoxicity and the generation of reactive oxygen species (ROS), as well as decreased the invasiveness. Treatment of TSGH 9201 cells with erinacine A resulted in the activation of caspases and the expression of TRAIL. Erinacine A induction of apoptosis was accompanied by sustained phosphorylation of FAK/AKT/p70S6K and the PAK1 pathways, as well as the generation of ROS. Furthermore, the induction of apoptosis and anti-invasion properties by erinacine A could involve the differential expression of the 14-3-3 sigma protein (1433S) and microtubule-associated tumor suppressor candidate 2 (MTUS2), with the activation of the FAK/AKT/p70S6K and PAK1 signaling pathways. Conclusions: These results lead us to speculate that erinacine A may generate an apoptotic cascade in TSGH 9201 cells by activating the FAK/AKT/p70S6K/PAK1 pathway and upregulating proteins 1433S and MTUS2, providing a new mechanism underlying the anti-cancer effects of erinacine A in human gastric cancer cells.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsing-Chun","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsing-Chun","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Yur-Ren","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Yur-Ren","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Yur-Ren","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Kam-Fai","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Kam-Fai","literal":""},{"family":"Hsieh","given":"Meng-Che","literal":""},{"family":"Hsieh","given":"Meng-Chiao","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Cheng-Yi","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Cheng-Yi","literal":""},{"family":"Hsieh","given":"Yung-Yu","literal":""},{"family":"Hsieh","given":"Yung-Yu","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Ko-Chao","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Ko-Chao","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsiang-Lan","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsiang-Lan","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li-Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li-Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wanping","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan-Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan-Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Chin-Chu","given":"Chen","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chin-Chu","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chin-Chu","literal":""},{"family":"Chin-Chu","given":"Chen","literal":""},{"family":"Tung","given":"Shui-Yi","literal":""},{"family":"Tung","given":"Shui-Yi","literal":""}],"citation-key":"kuo_comparative_2017","year":"2017","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["A Comparative Proteomic Analysis of Erinacine A's Inhibition of Gastric Cancer Cell Viability and Invasiveness."],"author-links":["[[Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo]]","[[Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo]]","[[Author/Yur-Ren Kuo]]","[[Author/Yur-Ren Kuo]]","[[Author/Yur-Ren Kuo]]","[[Author/Kam-Fai Lee]]","[[Author/Kam-Fai Lee]]","[[Author/Meng-Che Hsieh]]","[[Author/Meng-Chiao Hsieh]]","[[Author/Cheng-Yi Huang]]","[[Author/Cheng-Yi Huang]]","[[Author/Yung-Yu Hsieh]]","[[Author/Yung-Yu Hsieh]]","[[Author/Ko-Chao Lee]]","[[Author/Ko-Chao Lee]]","[[Author/Hsiang-Lan Kuo]]","[[Author/Hsiang-Lan Kuo]]","[[Author/Li-Ya Lee]]","[[Author/Li-Ya Lee]]","[[Author/Wanping Chen]]","[[Author/Wan-Ping Chen]]","[[Author/Wan-Ping Chen]]","[[Author/Chen Chin-Chu]]","[[Author/Chin-Chu Chen]]","[[Author/Chin-Chu Chen]]","[[Author/Chen Chin-Chu]]","[[Author/Shui-Yi Tung]]","[[Author/Shui-Yi Tung]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/kuo_comparative_2017/kuo_comparative_2017.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1qdmpr7","